1_Q31: I feel like if someone is suffering from acute schizophrenia, they're not able to truly make their own decisions because they're not in the headspace to do so. I kinda think about it like drinking, if one of my friends is drunk and they make a decision that could affect them long term (drive, sleep with someone, text or call someone they shouldn't talk to,) I do everything in my power to prevent that. Yes, people should always have free will and one's free will is something that no human should be able to disrupt, however, if someone isn't in the headspace to make a conscious decision, they shouldn't be able to decide their actions because they can't correctly estimate the consequences.
